President Obama has nominated Judge Evan Jonathan Wallach to the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit. Judge Wallach is currently a judge on the United States Court of International Trade. He has a distinguished legal career in both the public and private sectors and is known for his keen intellect and commitment to fairness and integrity. Judge Wallach served in the Vietnam War and was awarded the Bronze Star Medal. He completed his education at the University of Arizona and University of California at Berkeley's Boalt Hall School of Law. After law school, he joined a law firm in Las Vegas and later served as general counsel and public policy advisor to Senator Harry Reid. Judge Wallach has presided over more than 230 cases on international trade and customs law and has also sat on several federal trial and appellate courts.